<a href="/akira/dtd/2808-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_2808">Implement a policy wiki&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/4024-4049">michael</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">9 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Wikis help opinions converge on solutions and enable widespread participation. A policy wiki should require a verifiable registration for participants to deter abuse and create positive value for productive contributions.<br/>Wikis can expand into a network to include all issues and constituencies, making crucial citizen information available at one integrated and standardized site.<br/></div>
